ically only available in Pages view.  They provide quick information about page version history (so that you can easily rollback to an earlier version of a page, if need be, and site reports which detail pages that need urgent work or have not changed in a while.  </p>\n<h4>View Bar</h4>\n<p><strong>Location: On the very bottom of the screen.</strong></p>\n<p>The View Bar allows you to switch between the three views available within SilverStripe CMS: the editing view of the CMS, how your proposed website will look when and if it is published, and what the current, live, published page looks like.  Additionally, you can find on the right side of the View Bar a place to logout or alter your user profile. </p>', 'Basic Overview', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, 0, 2, NULL, 0, 0, 'Saved (update)', NULL, 'Anyone', 'LoggedInUsers', NULL, 1, '0.9'),
(193, 18, 6, 1, 1, 1, 'Page', '2010-06-01 14:04:30', '2010-06-01 16:40:37', 'creating-and-editing-content', 'Creating And Editing Content', NULL, '<h3>In this section:</h3>\n<p>\n</p><ul><li>Learn how to create a new page</li>\n<li>Learn how to write content for that page</li>\n<li>Learn how to describe that content for site navigation and search optimization</li>\n<li>Learn how to save your page as a draft</li>\n<li>Learn how to publish your page to the live site. </li>\n</ul><h3>Before We Begin:</h3>\n<p> </p>', 'Creating And Editing Content', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 0, 0, 'Saved (update)', NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', NULL, 5, '0.8'),
(194, 18, 7, 1, 1, 1, 'Page', '2010-06-01 14:04:30', '2010-06-01 16:41:57', 'creating-and-editing-content', 'Creating And Editing Content', NULL, '<h3>In this section:</h3>\n<ul><li>Learn how to create a new page</li>\n<li>Learn how to write content for that page</li>\n<li>Learn how to describe that content for site navigation and search optimization</li>\n<li>Learn how to save your page as a draft</li>\n<li>Learn how to publish your page to the live site. </li>\n</ul><h3>Before we begin:</h3>\n<p>\n</p><ul><li>Make sure you are in the "Pages" section on the Navigation Tabs. </li>\n</ul>', 'Creating And Editing Content', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 0, 0, 'Saved (update)', NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', NULL, 5, '0.8'),
(195, 18, 8, 0, 1, 0, 'Page', '2010-06-01 14:04:30', '2010-06-01 16:52:03', 'creating-and-editing-content', 'Creating And Editing Content', NULL, '<h3>In this section:</h3>\n<ul><li>Learn how to create a new page</li>\n<li>Learn how to write content for that page</li>\n<li>Learn how to describe that content for site navigation and search optimization</li>\n<li>Learn how to save your page as a draft</li>\n<li>Learn how to publish your page to the live site. </li>\n</ul><h3>Before we begin:</h3>\n<ul><li>Make sure you are in the "Pages" section on the Navigation Tabs. <br/>[ScreenShot]</li>\n</ul><h3>Creating a New Page:</h3>\n<p>To create a new page, first decide where in the site you want your page to be.  If you are creating a new "subpage," click on the parent page in the left-hand Contents Pane you would like to create the subpage in. If you want your site to be in the top level navigation for your site, you should click on the root of the site - the first item listed in the Contents Pane.  </p>\n<p>On the top of the Contents Pane, you will find a button marked "Create."  Click it, and a drop-down menu will show up.  The default selection should be "Page," but if it''s not, go ahead and select "Page."  Then hit the "Go" button. [Partial Screenshot]</p>\n<p>You will notice that a new page has been created, with the name of "New Page."  You will also notice it''s color, Yellow.  Yellow pages are "new" and have never been published. </p>\n<h5>Notes: </h5>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Don''t worry if you create your page in the "wrong" place.  Pages can be moved and re-ordered easily, and we will cover that under "Managing Your Site." </p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3>Writing Content:</h3>\n<h3>Describing Your Content:</h3>\n<h3>Saving Your Page as a Draft:</h3>\n<h3>Publishing Your Page:</h3>', 'Creating And Editing Content', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 0, 0, 'Saved (update)', NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', NULL, 5, '0.8'),
(196, 51, 1, 0, 1, 0, 'Page', '2010-06-01 16:52:12', '2010-06-01 16:52:12', 'new-page', 'New Page', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, 0, 5, NULL, 0, 0, 'New page', NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', NULL, 1, NULL),
