erce module, the Product page allows you to create a product that a person can purchase. <br/><br/>* <strong>Product Group</strong> - Included as part of the E-commerce module, the Product Group page allows you to group similar products together.</p>\n<h6>Forms:</h6>\n<p>* <strong>User Defined Form</strong> - This allows you to create a simple form for users, which can store data in the CMS, send an e-mail to a specified address, or both. Forms are covered in more detail in the "Forms" section of this document.</p>\n<h4>Changing an existing pagetype:</h4>\n<p>To change a pagetype, look in the Contents pane for the page you wish  to change. Click on it, and head to the "Behaviour" tab in the Editing  Pane. You can change the pagetype from the "Page type" drop-down menu.  Save your changes by pressing "Save" in the bottom right hand corner of  the editing pane.</p>\n<h3>Moving pages within the site:</h3>\n<p>To move a page within the site, head to the Contents pane on the left side of the screen. At the top of the content page should be a check-box next to "Allow drag &amp; drop reordering." By default, this should be turned off, in order to prevent errant clicks from altering the content of the site by accident. </p>\n<p>Clicking on that checkbox will enable drag and drop reordering, and you can move a page by clicking on it, and dragging it to its new position in the website.  After you are done moving pages, it''s a good idea to turn off the checkbox next to "Allow drag &amp; drop reordering." </p>\n<p>Relationships between pages:</p>\n<p>// Not sure about this, will come back to this later. If an end-user is reading this, please e-mail boyko@silverstripe.com and tell him he messed up on this page in the user documentation.</p>', 'Managing Your Site', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, 0, 3, NULL, 0, 0, 'Saved (update)', NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', NULL, 5, '0.9'),
(261, 9, 24, 1, 1, 1, 'Page', '2010-06-01 13:56:35', '2010-06-08 16:04:34', 'managing-your-site', 'Managing Your Site', NULL, '<h3>In this section:</h3>\n<ul><li>Learn the different content types</li>\n<li>Learn how to move pages within the site</li>\n<li>Learn the relationships between pages</li>\n<li>Learn how to hide a webpage</li>\n<li>Learn how to delete a webpage</li>\n<li>Learn how to view an old version of a page</li>\n<li>Learn how to rollback a web page to a previous version.</li>\n<li>Learn how to search for a page</li>\n<li>Learn how to publish or delete multiple pages</li>\n<li>Learn how to set content owners and review dates</li>\n<li>Learn how to add "To Do" items. </li>\n</ul><p><span style="font-family: Verdana, Lucida, Arial, sans-serif; font-size:  18px; color: #222222; font-weight: 300;">Before we begin:</span></p>\n<ul><li>Make sure you are in the "Pages" section on the Navigation  Tabs. </li>\n</ul><p><span style="line-height:  normal;">[ScreenShot]</span></p>\n<h3>Pagetypes:</h3>\n<p>There are many different types of pages in SilverStripe, each with its own functionality and purpose. By now you already know how to create a basic page. It is also possible to change a page from one pagetype to another.</p>\n<h4>Different pagetypes and their functions:</h4>\n<h6>Basic Pages:</h6>\n<p>* <strong>Page</strong> - The most basic pagetype. It contains content, and has no customised functionality or special purpose. Most pages you create on your site will be of this type. <br/><br/>* <strong>Home Page</strong> - The Home Page behaves like any other page, with the exception that it is the home page for your site - what users will see first if they browse directly to the root of your domain. <br/><br/>* <strong>Error Page</strong> - The page displayed when an error is produced by the website. Error pages can be created for individual error types, so for example, a 404 "Page not found" can look different from a 403 "Forbidden" page.<br/><br/>* <strong>Redirector to another page</strong> - This page on the website redirects the user to either another page on the same website, or a page on an external website.<br/><br/>* <strong>Virtual Page</strong> - A virtual page uses the content of another page. This is different from a redirector, as a redirector essentially links one location on the website to another, while a virtual page copies the content of the other page. Editing the page the virtual page is based on will, in turn, edit copied virtual page.</p>\n<h6>Blogs, Forums &amp; Mashups:</h6>\n<p>* <strong>Blog Holder</strong> - The blog holder acts as your main page for your site''s blog. Blog entries are always a subset of this page. <br/><br/>* <strong>Blog Entry</strong> - A blog entry is a page for a single entry on your blog. Blog entries are always a subpage of a Blog Holder page. <br/><br/>* <strong>Forum Holder</strong> - The forum holder acts as your main page for all your site''s forums. Forums are always a subset of this page.<br/><br/>* <strong>Forum</strong> - The forum is a page for a forum on your website, and holds all the discussion topics for a single forum. Forums are always a subpage of a Forum Holder page.<br/><br/>* <strong>Flickr Gallery</strong> - Part of the Flickr module, which allows you to pull images from Flickr to your site by matching your Group ID, Tag(s), or Photoset ID. <br/><br/>* <strong>YouTube Gallery</strong> - Part of the YouTube module, which allows you to display YouTube videos by matching your YouTube/Google Username, Tag(s), Search Phrase, or Playlist ID.</p>\n<h6>E-Commerce:</h6>\n<p>* <strong>Accounts Page</strong> - Included as part of the E-commerce module, the Accounts page allows the user to edit their E-commerce details.<br/><br/>* <strong>Checkout Page</strong> - Included as part of the E-commerce module, the Checkout page allows the user to edit their purchase and checkout, proceeding to payment.<br/><br/>* <strong>Product</strong> - Included as part of the E-commerce module, the Product page allows you to create a product that a person can purchase. <br/><br/>* <strong>Product Group</strong> - Included as part of the E-commerce module, the Product Group page allows you to group similar products together.</p>\n<h6>Forms:</h6>\n<p>* <strong>User Defined Form</strong> - This allows you to create a simple form for users, which can store data in the CMS, send an e-mail to a specified address, or both. Forms are covered in more detail in the "Forms" section of this document.</p>\n<h4>Changing an existing pagetype:</h4>\n<p>To change a pagetype, look in the Contents pane for the page you wish  to change. Click on it, and head to the "Behaviour" tab in the Editing  Pane. You can change the pagetype from the "Page type" drop-down menu.  Save your changes by pressing "Save" in the bottom right hand corner of  the editing pane.</p>\n<h3>Moving pages within the site:</h3>\n<p>To move a page within the site, head to the Contents pane on the left side of the screen. At the top of the content page should be a check-box next to "Allow drag &amp; drop reordering." By default, this should be turned off, in order to prevent errant clicks from altering the content of the site by accident. </p>\n<p>Clicking on that checkbox will enable drag and drop reordering, and you can move a page by clicking on it, and dragging it to its new position in the website.  After you are done moving pages, it''s a good idea to turn off the checkbox next to "Allow drag &amp; drop reordering." </p>\n<p>Relationships between pages:</p>\n<p>// Will come back to this later. If an end-user is reading this, please e-mail boyko@silverstripe.com and tell him he messed up on this page in the user documentation.</p>', 'Managing Your Site', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, 0, 3, NULL, 0, 0, 'Saved (update)', NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', NULL, 5, '0.9'),
