(281, 52, 2, 1, 1, 1, 'Page', '2010-06-11 10:27:19', '2010-06-11 10:27:35', 'content-review', 'Content Review', NULL, '<h3>Setting Content Owners and Review Dates:</h3>\n<h5>Notes:</h5>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Setting Content Owners is only possible if you have the "Workflow"  module installed.  Workflow is a module that is not part of the default  SilverStripe 2.4 installation, but it is supported.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>To set a content owner for a page, and give a review date for that  page which will generate an alert in the report section of the CMS when  that report is due, click on the page you wish to set a report for in  the Page Tree of the Contents pane. <br/><br/>Click on the "Review" tab in  the editing pane. Choose the page owner from the drop-down "Page owner"  menu. You can then set the review date using the built in calendar, and  if you want to have repeated reviews, you can change the frequency of  reviews by the drop-down box. This will alert the content owner via a  report in the CMS (viewable in the "Reports" section on the Navigation  Bar) and via e-mail.</p>', 'Content Review', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, 0, 10, NULL, 0, 0, 'Saved (new)', NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', NULL, 5, '0.8'),
(282, 52, 3, 0, 1, 0, 'Page', '2010-06-11 10:27:19', '2010-06-11 10:34:28', 'content-review', 'Content Review', NULL, '<h3>Setting Content Owners and Review Dates:</h3>\n<h5>Notes:</h5>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Setting Content Owners is only possible if you have the "Workflow"  module installed.  Workflow is a module that is not part of the default  SilverStripe 2.4 installation, but it is supported.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>To set a content owner for a page, and give a review date for that  page which will generate an alert in the report section of the CMS when  that report is due, click on the page you wish to set a report for in  the Page Tree of the Contents pane. <br/><br/>Click on the "Review" tab in  the editing pane. Choose the page owner from the drop-down "Page owner"  menu. You can then set the review date using the built in calendar, and  if you want to have repeated reviews, you can change the frequency of  reviews by the drop-down box. This will alert the content owner via a  report in the CMS (viewable in the "Reports" section on the Navigation  Bar) and via e-mail.</p>', 'Content Review', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, NULL, 0, 9, NULL, 0, 0, 'Saved (update)', NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', NULL, 5, '0.8'),
